<br>
Not everyone's ubered out, even in this day and age, nor is uber equipment necessary to do these areas that, in the past, no-one had Velious gear for.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, when I'm running around with my little evil enchanter (L 17 now), I marvel at how easy the zones she is exping in seem compared to when Nydia and Faervas were getting their butts handed to them daily.  Part of that is knowing the zones and your class capabilities better.  But a huge part of it is the fact that my alt is better dressed at 17 than Nydia was at 40...<br>
<br>
Unrest in full level 45 twink gear is a whole different experience than it is in a raw silk robe/banded &amp; rawhide and those uber +2 int &amp; +2 wis rings you just made yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Some people claim that the new additions to the game have 'dumbed it down' that much more at the lower levels.  It is true that the new corpse pre L 10 rules, and the avilability of rezzes at level 14 save a LOT of hiking.  But if you want to test out the game 'easiness' out, make an alt and level it from 1-20 with no outside equipment or levelling assistance whatsoever, and see if those lions don't still hit hard.  I've got a little ranger in thorn mail quest armor, a bronze shortsword, and scraps he looted off orc pawns, he looks just like the little green Sprout <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) who is getting his butt handed to him daily <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
<br>
EQ can be still be fun and challenging at all levels, even in the face of rampant mudflation.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  And to the newer players out there, as long as you are enjoying what you are doing, don't worry about how someone else plays *their* game...<br>
<br>
